19/08/2003
STARA ZAGORA, Bulgaria -- The United States will send experts to explore opportunities to open military bases in Bulgaria, Foreign Minister Solomon Passy said on Monday (18 August).
He added that he had received several requests from different municipalities, including Varna, Bourgas, Pleven, Plovdiv and Stara Zagora.
Some districts in the Rhodope Mountains also have expressed an interest.
Passy said the willingness of the local population would be taken into consideration before any location is approved.
In other news, a Bulgarian motorised infantry platoon has left to join the International Security Assistance Force in Afghanistan.
The unit will be under German command.
(Trud, 24 Chassa, Dnevnik - 19/08/03;
BTA, BNR, BNT - 18/08/03)
